                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="adambede_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">the first novel (1859) by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/george-eliot" title="George Eliot definition"><span class="ndv">George Eliot</span></a>. Adam Bede, a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/carpenter#carpenter_topg_1" title="carpenter definition"><span class="ndv">carpenter</span></a> in a village in the English <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/midlands" title="Midlands definition"><span class="ndv">Midlands</span></a>, falls in love with a beautiful young woman, but she has a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/tragic" title="tragic definition"><span class="ndv">tragic</span></a> affair with another man. Later, Adam falls in love with and marries her cousin, a good, calm and religious person.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
